        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1405736200" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5699767822445755979">Through his remarkable and dark-humorous writing, Banville lets his hero Freddie narrate or plead GUILTY to his jury/ audience - We, the readers - You, &quot;Who must have meaning in everything, who lusts after meaning, your palms sticky, and your faces on fire!&quot; It would be difficult not to think of Nabokov when you listen to self-pity story of Freddie and the way he addresses the readers or mocks them, at times.<br/><br/>Nevertheless, this is beautifully written and not lengthy. You would not be disappointed</span>
  <span id="freeText5699767822445755979" style="display:none">Through his remarkable and dark-humorous writing, Banville lets his hero Freddie narrate or plead GUILTY to his jury/ audience - We, the readers - You, "Who must have meaning in everything, who lusts after meaning, your palms sticky, and your faces on fire!" It would be difficult not to think of Nabokov when you listen to self-pity story of Freddie and the way he addresses the readers or mocks them, at times.<br /><br />Nevertheless, this is beautifully written and not lengthy. You would not be disappointed if you read this book of not much of an evidence.</span>
