<div id="review_2108578620" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2108578620" />
    <a title="Annette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/59105824-annette"><img alt="Annette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1472487704p2/59105824.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2108578620?book_show_action=true">Sep 18, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Annette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Annette" href="/user/show/59105824-annette">Annette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781447275367" href="/book/show/22946265-the-book-of-evidence">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2108578620" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5109775511532741789">This is already very, very funny. It simply is NOT THE POINT that this character is not a nice person, not likeable. Baffled by some of the other reviews that find this book unreadable because he&apos;s horrible. Hugely entertaining and so well written it hurts.<br/><br/>Compelling glimpse into the mind of a psychopath, the disconnect, the normality, the brutality. The killing of the maid is so well, and chillingly written. Banville really is an extraordinary writer. </span>
  <span id="freeText5109775511532741789" style="display:none">This is already very, very funny. It simply is NOT THE POINT that this character is not a nice person, not likeable. Baffled by some of the other reviews that find this book unreadable because he's horrible. Hugely entertaining and so well written it hurts.<br /><br />Compelling glimpse into the mind of a psychopath, the disconnect, the normality, the brutality. The killing of the maid is so well, and chillingly written. Banville really is an extraordinary writer. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5109775511532741789" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

